Jon, via _Greg to Differ_ , writes about the [role of social
media](http://gregtodiffer.com/home/2010/5/14/the-role-of-twitter-in-the-
bangkok-protests.html) in monitoring the Bangkok clashes

> Social media has played a major role in reporting the details of the Bangkok
> protests across the world. Powerful images, compelling video footage,
> personal accounts and opinion have been amplified by Twitter, Facebook and
> blogs to the point where social media is a valuable accompaniment to media
> reports.

